<paragraph id="4E401995DA1DD33F3B9D9DBA42D02EE5" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">
<emphasis id="5BD34459169FB3D9B1F79015A69BD372" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">Holotype</emphasis>
(BOLD &amp; TZU sample ID: ZJCH220; Field ID: BSZ87) 1 male, China, Zhejiang Province, Lishui City, Qingyuan County, Baishanzu National Nature Reserve, 
<geoCoordinate id="C55606FA064D6DB5EFC46D85D8273DD1" degrees="27.76" direction="north" orientation="latitude" precision="555" value="27.76">27.76°N</geoCoordinate>
, 
<geoCoordinate id="33139C3BC6E4140520964FD0530AD76E" degrees="119.31" direction="east" orientation="longitude" precision="555" value="119.31">119.31°E</geoCoordinate>
, 11-12. VIII. 2020, light trap, Qi X &amp; Song C. 
<emphasis id="3C911581E92E79947DA303133BBD57BC" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">Paratypes</emphasis>
: 2 males, same data as for holotype.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="0864A7ABC105C74D839BE6BE10930061" pageId="0" pageNumber="93" type="description">
<paragraph id="2F3F6F030444F23BE8C15599B7177373" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">Diagnostic characters.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="373D08DC20CD3BF77B6DA94FF48FD8DF" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">
The adult males of 
<taxonomicName id="A2DC09DF13F24635C3A76484C09D69B0" genus="S." lsidName="S. annulus" pageId="0" pageNumber="93" rank="species" species="annulus">
<emphasis id="60FCCD4697038C25A86B3CE705C87CB4" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">S. annulus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov. can be separated from known 
<taxonomicName id="CBC7085AD8416CD332706C0643460F18" authorityName="Kieffer" authorityYear="1919" class="Insecta" family="Chironomidae" genus="Stenochironomus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Stenochironomus" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="93" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="CAD61DF752CF5556282376C121A9D8B7" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">Stenochironomus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species from China by the following combination of characters: spots on the membrane of wing restricted to RM and FCu areas; posterior portion of median vittae with little pale pigmentation; lateral vittae with stripe markings; postnotum with markings reaching the posterior margin; femur of mid and hind legs with an 
<taxonomicName id="10955D4DA7B4E70EC7803A639E608C94" authorityName="Song &amp; Qi" authorityYear="2022" class="Insecta" family="Chironomidae" genus="Stenochironomus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Stenochironomus annulus" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="93" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="annulus">Stenochironomus annulus</taxonomicName>
medially on each; superior volsella cylindrical, with four long setae; inferior volsella extending beyond apex of anal point, with two or three bristles and one well-developed terminal spine.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="1E8612E40A4882DB90CD83190CD43E5D" pageId="0" pageNumber="93" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="C8FCB7B05F02C1747CA9D82E298BA5EF" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="BBCE06C1DCC9B9A4E04722F85048404A" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">The specific name refers to the circular ring markings of the femur of mid and hind legs of the male adult.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="EFF0C2C796D83BCFD072D7C56B50A238" pageId="0" pageNumber="93" type="description">
<paragraph id="12876F005528DA6F45AC9D3347C49807" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="EA2823FFE2FFDFCD7F895EE02A486DE8" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">Male imago (N = 3). Total length 3.59-4.17, 3.87 mm. Wing length 1.95-2.03, 2.00 mm. Total length / wing length 1.75-2.05, 1.94. Wing length / length of pro-femur 1.58-1.93, 1.73.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="760D04CB811010562373BD3EB233A0AB" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">
<emphasis id="4C8A29F86404D3A075C0195076D5EEF0" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">Coloration</emphasis>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation id="C02187F5D4A46D7A8A08E47A915629DD" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Male adult (holotype, in lateral view) of Stenochironomus annulus Song &amp; Qi sp. nov." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1104.81403.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/693995" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">3</figureCitation>
). Mature adult mostly brownish. Head yellow. Thorax yellowish except for the lateral vittae, postnotum with dark pigmentation and medial lateral with light pigmentation (sometimes difficult to observe). Membrane with 2 dark spots restricted to RM and FCu areas. Legs. Apical 3/5 of femur of P1 dark brown; apical and annulus of femur, and Ta 5 P2-P3 dark brown; basal 1/2 of tibia of P3 dark brown. Abdomen. Tergites V-IX brown.
</paragraph>
<caption id="D241AED36372719219261455599AA987" doi="10.3897/zookeys.1104.81403.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/693995" pageId="0" pageNumber="93" start="Figure 3" startId="F3">
<paragraph id="32729A473B74EA0CEBDE90A05CFCFE57" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">
<emphasis id="299338AFA9F6EB498E5BF2B733DDBBD0" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">Figure 3.</emphasis>
Male adult (holotype, in lateral view) of 
<taxonomicName id="CFB9714C46FC6AFB0238EBE763D89D75" authorityName="Song &amp; Qi" authorityYear="2022" class="Insecta" family="Chironomidae" genus="Stenochironomus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Stenochironomus annulus" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="93" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="annulus">
<emphasis id="59C1978A79AB073AF2BB3E36CAD16C23" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">Stenochironomus annulus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Song &amp; Qi sp. nov.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="AEB19C661417FCEEF87D8D1FC45C6FEE" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">
<emphasis id="0AB28FA335E1CF4E8AA33B756A9A74E8" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">
<emphasis id="937B9A966A7B515B5C03C947F984E361" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">Head</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
AR 1.62-1.88 (2), ultimate flagellomere 680-770 
<normalizedToken id="1D783F2639133FA50A63EC90141A5276" originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
long; Temporals 10-13, 12 setae including 5-8 inner, and 2-3 outer, verticals, postorbitals 1-3. Clypeus with 15-22, 19 setae. Tentorium 170-205 
<normalizedToken id="6DC17285E28D2F3D43BE5E0ACA42B8AC" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
long, 45-53 
<normalizedToken id="10D87C83B7F829F919F64B0D356F19E7" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
wide at the widest part. Palp 5-segmented, lengths (in 
<normalizedToken id="C2116D854A8DE019416FC64E0F7482B7" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
) of segments: 60-70, 66; 50-70, 60; 193-220, 203; 140-160, 152; 208-288, 248. Palpomere ratio (5th / 3rd) 1.09-1.31, 1.22.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="25B75312AAEC925315927E4B15E72887" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">
<emphasis id="4A5CDE4EC6C39C5AE3097B9E50490E2D" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">
<emphasis id="CE799B7B1D5D8C32DE90A71884131D73" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">Thorax</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Dorsocentrals 16-17, 18; acrostichals 12-15, 14; prealars 5-6, 6; Scutellum with 11-13 setae in 2 rows.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="37D821684A2B01AD6E56C1ADA15955FE" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">
<emphasis id="5CF32D437006253B882FF3F003F1B845" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">Wing</emphasis>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation id="29B261196E7519CD5B9900E18D85F9D6" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Male adult of Stenochironomus annulus Song &amp; Qi, sp. nov. A wing B hypopygium in dorsal view C hypopygium in ventral view D legs." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1104.81403.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/693996" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">4A</figureCitation>
). VR 1.08-1.08, 1.06. Brachiolum with 2-3 setae. Distribution of setae on veins: R, 31-39, 34; R1, 28-40, 34; R4+5, 33-62, 46. Squama with 8-12, 10 setae. Anal lobe normally developed.
</paragraph>
<caption id="778658B384366EE5CB67A2E00EBA349F" doi="10.3897/zookeys.1104.81403.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/693996" pageId="0" pageNumber="93" start="Figure 4" startId="F4">
<paragraph id="D6FC389B8F5B5C99EFAFEDA4161F58F2" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">
<emphasis id="0B5F08AC9AA10471486AD85ABE007ED2" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">Figure 4.</emphasis>
Male adult of 
<taxonomicName id="A99B27CBF3259FBF096BA0F6C90ABDF6" authorityName="Song &amp; Qi" authorityYear="2022" class="Insecta" family="Chironomidae" genus="Stenochironomus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Stenochironomus annulus" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="93" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="annulus">
<emphasis id="68C3198CFBC0E64BA75A84ED870417F8" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">Stenochironomus annulus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Song &amp; Qi, sp. nov. 
<emphasis id="D50DF25BAC31F1D5E84CEA3F68E94B02" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">A</emphasis>
wing 
<emphasis id="C1FE4E209DBACB28E5439A2D5F701A79" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">B</emphasis>
hypopygium in dorsal view 
<emphasis id="F7DA8119DAED5E4D3F4CCBE71746B5A5" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">C</emphasis>
hypopygium in ventral view 
<emphasis id="9FDF4F4A3C30D340541515F41F89D8FF" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">D</emphasis>
legs.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="9925563E5AE5939B739F448FF634FE83" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">
<emphasis id="7D750F46756E448C7C648CA6A8731CFF" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">Legs</emphasis>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation id="333682A913ADE707E14BDAC001C80670" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Male adult of Stenochironomus annulus Song &amp; Qi, sp. nov. A wing B hypopygium in dorsal view C hypopygium in ventral view D legs." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1104.81403.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/693996" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">4D</figureCitation>
). Fore leg: width at apex of tibia 43-50, 46 
<normalizedToken id="F60334C9D0DD9387A55BF6D1085D3369" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
, tibia with blunt scale 35-40, 38 
<normalizedToken id="6B7CBDB68F4A209990B25152AF8C3123" originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
long. Mid leg: width at apex of tibia 53-65, 59 
<normalizedToken id="BFD7F83E513DBDBAD0192B33F9BF4454" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
, tibia with 2 apical spurs 35-38, 37 and 40-45, 43 
<normalizedToken id="961F7F3190464B4B99E056EA87A94FC1" originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
long. Hind leg: tibia 60-73 
<normalizedToken id="95D23BC2BD503331D25BAA55DC1335E6" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
width at apex; tibial spurs 40-43, 42 and 40-43, 42 
<normalizedToken id="A32759A79F8F85DDF4494773E39CD481" originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
long, slightly fused medially. Lengths (in 
<normalizedToken id="381E1B8CE3D838C77E0D406C8B98F870" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
) and proportions of legs in Table 
