<paragraph id="981BD5150EC382787C38408BAE29D495" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">
<emphasis id="D30C2F1C6564DB65EE70B78DA3760250" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">Hypopygium</emphasis>
(Figs 
<figureCitation id="80273C7592BC4593F4F58085D0D5D618" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Male adult of Stenochironomus annulus Song &amp; Qi, sp. nov. A wing B hypopygium in dorsal view C hypopygium in ventral view D legs." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1104.81403.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/693996" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">4B, C</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="153D2A925FAD2C99CB4A55A57992FF5A" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figure 5. Male adult (holotype) of Stenochironomus annulus Song &amp; Qi sp. nov. A hypopygium in dorsal view B hypopygium in ventral view C superior volsella." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1104.81403.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/693997" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">5</figureCitation>
). Anal point straight and parallel-sided in dorsal view, 103-113, 100 
<normalizedToken id="C2B19174391BC7BA8048EED118E0BDF6" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
long and 30-43, 35 
<normalizedToken id="DBE1669A044E2F8B959EC9F7E110135A" originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
wide at base, 8-10, 9 
<normalizedToken id="BC8507BA2E1AA1F91C1A37D2FED94D2C" originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
wide at apex. Tergite IX with 19-22, 20 long setae medially and posterior margin of tergite IX with 6 strong setae and 5 spines. Laterosternite IX with 4-4, 4 setae. Transverse sternapodeme 43-50, 47 
<normalizedToken id="9DE54A075B0A66196DF38A10CDF7F16B" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
long; phallapodeme 78-88, 85 
<normalizedToken id="9FE27153F8F351915B98444A29474DD1" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
long. Gonocoxite 173-185, 181 
<normalizedToken id="5AC7B327C0AA3E906BC71AC3E3B81E91" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
long, gonostylus 205-270, 238 
<normalizedToken id="48B850BD837E2442F44ADBFAD0B5AF7B" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
long. Superior volsella cylindrical, 40-45, 43 
<normalizedToken id="E5269DCC488B8612177BC81B568CEDDB" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
long, 20-20, 20 
<normalizedToken id="F6175654751B74375BEA69A970D78BBD" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
wide, with 4-5 long setae (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="783351EC7CCADF1E39F96BDBA7837691" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Male adult of Stenochironomus annulus Song &amp; Qi, sp. nov. A wing B hypopygium in dorsal view C hypopygium in ventral view D legs." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1104.81403.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/693996" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">4C</figureCitation>
). Inferior volsella elongate, 203-228 
<normalizedToken id="702EF9EC1ABC664924B45AEE1C02077C" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
long, extending beyond the apex of anal point, with 2-3 long bristles and 1 strong terminal spine. HR 0.64-0.90, 0.77, HV 1.46-1.75, 1.64.
</paragraph>
<caption id="C02A39C87401B6E8C9B676B7EFDDDFDF" doi="10.3897/zookeys.1104.81403.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/693997" pageId="0" pageNumber="93" start="Figure 5" startId="F5">
<paragraph id="032082566B639E6DFBC485C1DD801E31" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">
<emphasis id="597A595BD655924A615A823B4624EB4B" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">Figure 5.</emphasis>
Male adult (holotype) of 
<taxonomicName id="C7FC2609D90B9BB1DC542B55DF4F5A49" authorityName="Song &amp; Qi" authorityYear="2022" class="Insecta" family="Chironomidae" genus="Stenochironomus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Stenochironomus annulus" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="93" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="annulus">
<emphasis id="4689AA7EBF27F9729FC76640D3CC0E49" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">Stenochironomus annulus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Song &amp; Qi sp. nov. 
<emphasis id="C9596BD34D1A0CBB90BAF4CBA7FA0C23" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">A</emphasis>
hypopygium in dorsal view 
<emphasis id="A05B1255CD7A798F7E67F63F82D5102A" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">B</emphasis>
hypopygium in ventral view 
<emphasis id="5ECCF3514BC4B70C766D275F315ED348" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">C</emphasis>
superior volsella.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="2C61961FAE13D631AE730BD5F01E6C12" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">Immature stages and female unknown.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="9B210263EFC4C5833E24B74D8C7B451A" pageId="0" pageNumber="93" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="0A26212B6AD0DAD563EA7FA63FD8202F" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A6359E65A539D9F0433E59A83E11816D" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">
Morphologically, 
<taxonomicName id="9CC9B3D103970E87CAA448275FF092A0" genus="S." lsidName="S. annulus" pageId="0" pageNumber="93" rank="species" species="annulus">
<emphasis id="A5F98EF897EC64929BE0F56BB74074BA" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">S. annulus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov. shows high similarity to 
<taxonomicName id="51DFFF9D9017ADB8F000B6220194FDBC" class="Insecta" family="Chironomidae" genus="Stenochironomus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Stenochironomus xianjuensis" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="93" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="xianjuensis">
<emphasis id="A5819EBBCD1E935A414891C51452EEF3" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">Stenochironomus xianjuensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Zhang, Gu, Qi &amp; Wang, 2016, on the basis of the following similar common characters: membrane of wing with similar spot patterns; cylindrical superior and inferior volsella. However, the new described species could be distinguished in having a straight and parallel-sided anal point and different leg pigmentation patterns. According to the molecular data, 
<taxonomicName id="E1D140D60CAE8A3F99FD4F3D58A6232E" genus="S." lsidName="S. annulus" pageId="0" pageNumber="93" rank="species" species="annulus">
<emphasis id="45BB3F8D021E81C54876995334FB253F" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">S. annulus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is sister to 
<taxonomicName id="3E2510CB526F1B7AF63C3C7F58D45093" genus="S." lsidName="S. gibbus" pageId="0" pageNumber="93" rank="species" species="gibbus">
<emphasis id="D37C980DB16668AF1B210600B77D9B59" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">S. gibbus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation id="93A662CB12F8FC56CE87BFC750E28A18" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Neighbour-joining tree for twelve species of Stenochironomus based on K 2 P distance in DNA barcodes. Clade in yellow represents S. annulus sp. nov., red represents S. baishanzuensis sp. nov. Numbers on branches represent bootstrap support (&gt; 75 %) based on 1000 replicates; scale equals K 2 P genetic distance." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1104.81403.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/693993" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">1</figureCitation>
), but could be separated by thorax vittate and leg coloration (Table 
<tableCitation id="EDB6EABF3AE4810579136ECC83A6DA80" captionStart="Table 4" captionStartId="T4" captionText="Table 4. Main differences between S. annulus sp. nov., S. baishanzuensis sp. nov., S. gibbus, and S. xianjuensis." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/75B996484767B660C9AD7B2025EBC620" pageId="0" pageNumber="93" tableUuid="75B996484767B660C9AD7B2025EBC620">4</tableCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption id="75B996484767B660C9AD7B2025EBC620" ID-Table-UUID="75B996484767B660C9AD7B2025EBC620" httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/75B996484767B660C9AD7B2025EBC620" pageId="0" pageNumber="93" start="Table 4" startId="T4">
<paragraph id="FC65CB782DDB6B067C0256C0FE059D2F" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">
<emphasis id="0E2176B7A0EBD71AE406FA43D021F451" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">Table 4.</emphasis>
Main differences between 
<taxonomicName id="4A8D9A4073C0E971E44F8898000B8491" genus="S." lsidName="S. annulus" pageId="0" pageNumber="93" rank="species" species="annulus">
<emphasis id="FCE990986BD4C3B557645CB366E32BAC" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">S. annulus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov., 
<taxonomicName id="2860DAFFFA7DCC3E077C4F1F4F4E651F" genus="S." lsidName="S. baishanzuensis" pageId="0" pageNumber="93" rank="species" species="baishanzuensis">
<emphasis id="92EFB095D013BFA1F57D114398040D0E" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">S. baishanzuensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov., 
<taxonomicName id="BD2E3C18618B4E483CA938F1BAC65515" genus="S." lsidName="S. gibbus" pageId="0" pageNumber="93" rank="species" species="gibbus">
<emphasis id="ABF64BFB3D46371DCAEC0BDBAC94A700" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">S. gibbus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="E91711BDC8BA45176E9171A82AD14AA6" genus="S." lsidName="S. xianjuensis" pageId="0" pageNumber="93" rank="species" species="xianjuensis">
<emphasis id="786A5ECCC6AF8EC23B5D7100AFA2BB5F" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">S. xianjuensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="E12C48773CFAB26BE4710C28942698B1" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">
<table id="568962E1BF3CE41F8AA36BF036D7915D" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">
